01:12.407 --> 01:14.908
The whole world is on fire,
starting with my office.

01:14.993 --> 01:17.394
We've had to completely
reevaluate

01:17.445 --> 01:18.779
all our security
measures

01:18.863 --> 01:22.399
after what that woman did.

01:22.450 --> 01:24.234
The truth is...

01:24.285 --> 01:26.503
I wanted to give you time
to collect your thoughts.

01:26.571 --> 01:29.706
I know when there's something
you want to talk about.

01:35.630 --> 01:37.564
I'm in love with Peter.

01:37.632 --> 01:40.750
I know it sounds absurd
to you.

01:40.802 --> 01:42.519
I hardly know him.

01:42.587 --> 01:46.523
But it's like I've known him
my entire life.

01:46.591 --> 01:47.858
And everybody,
including him,

01:47.925 --> 01:50.894
keeps telling me
that it's impossible.

01:50.945 --> 01:52.780
When Walter told me
what you were going through--

01:52.864 --> 01:55.599
two sets of memories,
two sets of experiences--

01:55.650 --> 01:58.769
he said the Cortexiphan dosing
might be enabling you

01:58.837 --> 02:01.221
to remember things that
Peter wants you to remember.

02:01.289 --> 02:03.907
But I can remember things
that Peter couldn't have known,

02:03.958 --> 02:06.443
like details of cases
that he wasn't on

02:06.494 --> 02:10.881
or names, um,
places he's never been.

02:10.948 --> 02:15.219
I mean, how can that be
if--if he's controlling it?

02:15.286 --> 02:17.954
<i>I don't know how</i>
<i>this is happening,</i>

02:18.006 --> 02:21.725
but...

02:21.792 --> 02:24.561
I'm scared.

02:26.347 --> 02:28.765
We're gonna figure out what's
happening with you, Olive.

02:28.817 --> 02:31.985
Now, as for your feelings
about Peter,

02:32.070 --> 02:34.271
all wounds heal
over time.

02:34.322 --> 02:37.774
Yeah. I just wish the time
would move a little quicker.

02:37.826 --> 02:39.076
Well, that's a coincidence,

02:39.143 --> 02:42.913
because we just filed a patent
on that last week.

02:42.980 --> 02:46.316
It's good to be with you.
We should do this more often.

02:48.453 --> 02:50.838
What's wrong?

02:50.922 --> 02:53.757
We always have
breakfast together

02:53.824 --> 02:56.593
on Saturday mornings.

02:56.661 --> 03:00.497
We were here last week.

03:00.548 --> 03:04.384
Are you saying
you don't remember?

03:06.604 --> 03:09.022
I'm worried.

03:09.107 --> 03:12.893
You're having these experiences
at what cost?

03:23.454 --> 03:25.572
I'll talk to Walter.

03:40.054 --> 03:41.171
<i>Hey, Jane, it's Celia.</i>

03:41.222 --> 03:43.557
<i>God, it was</i>
<i>a beautiful service...</i>

03:45.593 --> 03:52.983
♪ ♪

03:53.050 --> 03:56.270
<i>If you need anything,</i>
<i>please call us.</i>

04:27.602 --> 04:29.136
Who are you?

04:31.922 --> 04:33.724
What do you want?

04:39.113 --> 04:40.814
No, please don't!

04:40.898 --> 04:44.934
No, please don't!

05:31.949 --> 05:33.650
No...

05:35.453 --> 05:38.255
No! No!

06:27.320 --> 06:31.320
